{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17651075","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17651075"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T21:19:37+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T21:19:37+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18428"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18428","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18428"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11146"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74564"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11146","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11146"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18428"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60055"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4940"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"8424"},{"type":"tags","id":"10147"},{"type":"tags","id":"10248"},{"type":"tags","id":"10249"},{"type":"tags","id":"10257"},{"type":"tags","id":"10260"},{"type":"tags","id":"10261"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25829"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25831"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74564","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74564"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following muscle proteins provides the elastic component of skeletal muscle and helps stabilize the position of thick and thin filaments?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Relaxin","Tropomodulin","Desmin","Titin","Alpha-actinin"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETitin\u003C/strong\u003E is a large protein that spans half of the sarcomere, from the Z-disc to the M-line. It acts as a molecular spring, providing passive elasticity to muscle and maintaining the structural integrity of the sarcomere. Titin helps stabilize the position of thick and thin filaments during muscle contraction and relaxation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERelaxin\u003C/strong\u003E is a hormone involved in pregnancy and does not play a role in muscle elasticity or filament stabilization.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETropomodulin\u003C/strong\u003E is a protein that caps the pointed end of actin filaments, regulating their length but not contributing to elasticity or stabilization of thick filaments.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDesmin\u003C/strong\u003E is an intermediate filament protein that helps maintain the structural integrity of muscle cells by linking the contractile apparatus to the cell membrane, but it does not provide elasticity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAlpha-actinin\u003C/strong\u003E is a protein that cross-links actin filaments at the Z-disc, providing structural support but not contributing to the elastic properties of muscle.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Titin is a large protein that contributes to the elasticity of muscle and helps stabilize the position of thick and thin filaments.","Titin acts as a molecular spring, providing passive elasticity to muscle and maintaining the structural integrity of the sarcomere."],"references":["Patton, K. T., \u0026 Thibodeau, G. A. (2018). Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book: Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press",